WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:24.298 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:24.298 --> 00:00:26.090 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:27.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm George Noory.

00:00:27.020 --> 00:00:30.650 align:middle line:10%
And this program will be a very
heart warming program for you.

00:00:30.650 --> 00:00:34.100 align:middle line:10%
After a four year battle with
that dreaded disease, cancer,

00:00:34.100 --> 00:00:37.010 align:middle line:10%
Anita Moorjani fell
into a coma and was

00:00:37.010 --> 00:00:38.780 align:middle line:10%
given just days to live.

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:41.600 align:middle line:84%
As her doctors gathered
to try to revive her,

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:44.027 align:middle line:84%
something magnificent
happened to her

00:00:44.027 --> 00:00:45.860 align:middle line:84%
and we're going to have
her tell that story.

00:00:45.860 --> 00:00:47.460 align:middle line:84%
Anita, welcome to
"Beyond Belief."

00:00:47.460 --> 00:00:48.960 align:middle line:84%
>>ANITA MOORJANI:
Thank you so much.

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:50.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's go
back a little bit,

00:00:50.460 --> 00:00:54.530 align:middle line:84%
if it's not too painful for
you, to tell us what happened.

00:00:54.530 --> 00:00:57.080 align:middle line:84%
How did doctors
diagnose your cancer

00:00:57.080 --> 00:00:59.900 align:middle line:84%
and then how did
you react to them?

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So I was
dealing with lymphoma.

00:01:02.180 --> 00:01:07.640 align:middle line:84%
It started with just a
lump on my neck and over--

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.920 align:middle line:84%
and it was diagnosed
as lymphoma.

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:12.950 align:middle line:84%
At the time they diagnosed
it, it was stage two.

00:01:12.950 --> 00:01:15.560 align:middle line:10%
But over a period
of four years, I

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:18.150 align:middle line:10%
tried many different
modalities to try and heal it.

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:18.950 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:01:18.950 --> 00:01:21.410 align:middle line:10%
>>MOORJANI: At first I was
against the chemotherapy

00:01:21.410 --> 00:01:23.780 align:middle line:10%
and I wanted to go
for alternative.

00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:27.230 align:middle line:10%
But the doctors kept pushing
me towards chemotherapy.

00:01:27.230 --> 00:01:30.410 align:middle line:84%
But everything I
tried wasn't working.

00:01:30.410 --> 00:01:33.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was so afraid
of this cancer.

00:01:33.410 --> 00:01:35.000 align:middle line:90%
I feared cancer.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:38.840 align:middle line:84%
I feared-- I feared the
treatments for cancer.

00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:40.160 align:middle line:90%
And I feared death.

00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:44.060 align:middle line:84%
So I was living in this
constant state of fear.

00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:46.940 align:middle line:84%
As I was trying all the
alternative modalities,

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:50.780 align:middle line:84%
I was really paranoid
about what I was eating,

00:01:50.780 --> 00:01:52.830 align:middle line:84%
and what I was ingesting,
and what I was doing.

00:01:52.830 --> 00:01:53.630 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:01:53.630 --> 00:01:55.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: It was like
a really fearful time.

00:01:55.580 --> 00:01:59.120 align:middle line:84%
And it felt as though things
would work for a little while

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:00.930 align:middle line:90%
and then it wouldn't work.

00:02:00.930 --> 00:02:03.020 align:middle line:90%
And so the cancer progressed.

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:08.000 align:middle line:84%
And it started in
2002, and by 2005, I

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:10.190 align:middle line:84%
decided I'll go for
the chemotherapy.

00:02:10.190 --> 00:02:14.090 align:middle line:84%
And so when they
did the test on me,

00:02:14.090 --> 00:02:16.340 align:middle line:90%
they said that it's too late.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:18.650 align:middle line:84%
Even for the chemotherapy,
it's too late.

00:02:18.650 --> 00:02:19.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, gosh.

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:23.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And they gave
me the chemotherapy anyway.

00:02:23.630 --> 00:02:27.410 align:middle line:84%
But what most people said was
that this is just going to--

00:02:27.410 --> 00:02:29.270 align:middle line:90%
your body can't even handle it.

00:02:29.270 --> 00:02:30.560 align:middle line:90%
It's too weak.

00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:34.400 align:middle line:84%
What ended up happening, though,
is that I went into a coma.

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:36.410 align:middle line:84%
But I just want to
describe at this point,

00:02:36.410 --> 00:02:38.580 align:middle line:90%
this was February 2006--

00:02:38.580 --> 00:02:39.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:42.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And the condition
of my physical body.

00:02:42.110 --> 00:02:45.140 align:middle line:84%
What had started out
as a lump on my neck,

00:02:45.140 --> 00:02:48.110 align:middle line:84%
now, because it had
spread and metastasized

00:02:48.110 --> 00:02:52.160 align:middle line:84%
throughout my lymphatic system,
I had tumors, some of them

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:53.337 align:middle line:90%
the size of golf balls--

00:02:53.337 --> 00:02:54.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, my God.

00:02:54.170 --> 00:02:58.040 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: From the base of
my skull, all around my neck,

00:02:58.040 --> 00:02:59.330 align:middle line:90%
under my arms.

00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:00.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It was in your
blood system, wasn't it?

00:03:00.830 --> 00:03:01.160 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:02.160 align:middle line:90%
It was everywhere.

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:03.350 align:middle line:90%
It was in my--

00:03:03.350 --> 00:03:06.650 align:middle line:84%
and the tumors were in my
chest and in all the way

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:07.550 align:middle line:90%
down to my abdomen.

00:03:07.550 --> 00:03:08.350 align:middle line:90%
All around.

00:03:08.350 --> 00:03:09.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were they
all malignant?

00:03:09.950 --> 00:03:11.210 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: All malignant.

00:03:11.210 --> 00:03:16.712 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, also, my
lungs were filled with fluid.

00:03:16.712 --> 00:03:18.170 align:middle line:84%
They would develop
fluid, which had

00:03:18.170 --> 00:03:20.415 align:middle line:84%
to be drained every
two to three weeks,

00:03:20.415 --> 00:03:22.040 align:middle line:84%
and then they would
fill up with fluid.

00:03:22.040 --> 00:03:23.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or you'd get pneumonia.

00:03:23.270 --> 00:03:23.555 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:03:23.555 --> 00:03:24.847 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or that would get you.

00:03:24.847 --> 00:03:28.490 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And I was breathing
with the aid of oxygen

00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:32.870 align:middle line:84%
because I was, like, out
of breath all the time.

00:03:32.870 --> 00:03:35.930 align:middle line:84%
My body stopped
absorbing nutrition,

00:03:35.930 --> 00:03:38.190 align:middle line:90%
so I weighed about 85 pounds.

00:03:38.190 --> 00:03:38.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh.

00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:39.940 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I was
like a skeleton.

00:03:39.940 --> 00:03:41.273 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So you were near death?

00:03:41.273 --> 00:03:43.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I was
literally near death

00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:46.370 align:middle line:84%
even before I went
into the coma.

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:48.080 align:middle line:90%
And I was--

00:03:48.080 --> 00:03:49.010 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't walk.

00:03:49.010 --> 00:03:51.800 align:middle line:84%
So my mobility came in
the form of a wheelchair.

00:03:51.800 --> 00:03:54.920 align:middle line:84%
When I would lie down,
I would choke because

00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:56.300 align:middle line:90%
of the fluid in my lungs.

00:03:56.300 --> 00:03:57.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, my God.

00:03:57.470 --> 00:04:00.770 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And so on
February 2, I went into a coma

00:04:00.770 --> 00:04:02.970 align:middle line:90%
because my organs shut down.

00:04:02.970 --> 00:04:06.530 align:middle line:84%
That was when the doctors
actually said to my family

00:04:06.530 --> 00:04:08.550 align:middle line:84%
that I won't even make
it through the night.

00:04:08.550 --> 00:04:09.550 align:middle line:90%
They said I won't even--

00:04:09.550 --> 00:04:10.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You won't even revive?

00:04:10.850 --> 00:04:12.890 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I won't even
revive from the coma.

00:04:12.890 --> 00:04:15.020 align:middle line:84%
I won't even make it
through the night.

00:04:15.020 --> 00:04:18.260 align:middle line:84%
But unbeknownst to
everyone around me,

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:21.050 align:middle line:84%
while I was in the
coma, that was when

00:04:21.050 --> 00:04:24.650 align:middle line:90%
I felt that I had left my body.

00:04:24.650 --> 00:04:26.550 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me
that experience.

00:04:26.550 --> 00:04:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So what
happened was that--

00:04:28.970 --> 00:04:32.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were you aware
you were in a coma?

00:04:32.300 --> 00:04:33.920 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: I was aware that--

00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:39.020 align:middle line:84%
I actually was aware that I
was dying, but not immediately.

00:04:39.020 --> 00:04:43.970 align:middle line:84%
I started to actually feel
like the pain was gone.

00:04:43.970 --> 00:04:46.130 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened
is literally the night

00:04:46.130 --> 00:04:49.070 align:middle line:84%
before I went into a
coma, I was feeling

00:04:49.070 --> 00:04:53.788 align:middle line:84%
in so much pain, so much
discomfort, so much fear.

00:04:53.788 --> 00:04:54.830 align:middle line:90%
Because I couldn't sleep.

00:04:54.830 --> 00:04:56.740 align:middle line:84%
If I slept, I
would start choking

00:04:56.740 --> 00:04:57.740 align:middle line:90%
and it would wake me up.

00:04:57.740 --> 00:04:58.698 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's horrible.

00:04:58.698 --> 00:05:00.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: It
was just horrible.

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:02.990 align:middle line:84%
And then, I had been
fighting for four years.

00:05:02.990 --> 00:05:03.980 align:middle line:90%
Fighting the cancer.

00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:05.450 align:middle line:90%
Fighting to stay alive.

00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:07.790 align:middle line:84%
But I had reached a point
where it felt like this

00:05:07.790 --> 00:05:09.570 align:middle line:90%
wasn't worth fighting for.

00:05:09.570 --> 00:05:11.720 align:middle line:84%
I knew death couldn't
be worse than this.

00:05:11.720 --> 00:05:14.490 align:middle line:84%
So I felt as though
I just surrendered.

00:05:14.490 --> 00:05:15.290 align:middle line:90%
I just gave up.

00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:16.090 align:middle line:90%
I surrendered.

00:05:16.090 --> 00:05:17.790 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, take me.

00:05:17.790 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:90%
Literally, I--

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:19.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You were ready to go?

00:05:19.250 --> 00:05:20.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: I was ready to go.

00:05:20.060 --> 00:05:22.110 align:middle line:84%
I said it's not worth
living like this.

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:23.660 align:middle line:90%
I was ready to go.

00:05:23.660 --> 00:05:25.990 align:middle line:84%
I fell asleep when
I surrendered.

00:05:25.990 --> 00:05:29.760 align:middle line:84%
But I think from sleep
I went into this coma.

00:05:29.760 --> 00:05:32.430 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I know
I went into the coma

00:05:32.430 --> 00:05:35.320 align:middle line:84%
was because that's
when I left my body.

00:05:35.320 --> 00:05:38.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So when you're in
this out of body experience--

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:38.880 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:40.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Your body's in a coma?

00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:05:40.380 --> 00:05:41.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're floating above.

00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:43.230 align:middle line:90%
Are you looking at that body?

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:44.030 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:45.030 align:middle line:90%
I could see that body.

00:05:45.030 --> 00:05:48.450 align:middle line:84%
And yet, it didn't feel
like I was an entity.

00:05:48.450 --> 00:05:50.700 align:middle line:90%
It felt like I was bigger.

00:05:50.700 --> 00:05:56.225 align:middle line:84%
And it was like I had 360
degree peripheral vision.

00:05:56.225 --> 00:05:58.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did you think you
were dead at that point?

00:05:58.350 --> 00:05:58.470 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: I did.

00:05:58.470 --> 00:05:59.370 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You did.

00:05:59.370 --> 00:06:01.590 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I thought my
physical body was dead.

00:06:01.590 --> 00:06:03.300 align:middle line:90%
I could see my body.

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:06.285 align:middle line:84%
I could see my family,
my mom, my husband.

00:06:06.285 --> 00:06:07.410 align:middle line:90%
I could see them gathered--

00:06:07.410 --> 00:06:07.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Gathered around you--

00:06:07.800 --> 00:06:08.475 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Gathered around.

00:06:08.475 --> 00:06:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Crying and
everything else?

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:09.450 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Crying.

00:06:09.450 --> 00:06:10.410 align:middle line:90%
And the doctors.

00:06:10.410 --> 00:06:15.150 align:middle line:84%
And I heard the doctors
tell my husband that--

00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:17.317 align:middle line:84%
that she-- that her
organs have now shut down

00:06:17.317 --> 00:06:18.900 align:middle line:84%
and she's not going
to come out of it.

00:06:18.900 --> 00:06:19.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, you were dying.

00:06:19.470 --> 00:06:20.270 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:06:20.270 --> 00:06:22.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You were-- the dying
process is under way for you.

00:06:22.920 --> 00:06:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:06:23.430 --> 00:06:25.888 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the doctors
were making clear to my family.

00:06:25.888 --> 00:06:27.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How long were
you in this coma type?

00:06:27.990 --> 00:06:29.610 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: About 30 hours.

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:31.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of human hours.

00:06:31.010 --> 00:06:32.010 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Human hours.

00:06:32.010 --> 00:06:33.373 align:middle line:90%
It was 30 human hours.

00:06:33.373 --> 00:06:35.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Our dear
friend, Raymond Moody,

00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:38.610 align:middle line:84%
who is an expert researcher
on near-death experiences,

00:06:38.610 --> 00:06:40.792 align:middle line:84%
was on the Gaia
series, "Legacy."

00:06:40.792 --> 00:06:42.120 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:06:42.120 --> 00:06:43.920 align:middle line:10%
>>RAYMOND MOODY:
Near-death experiences

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:47.940 align:middle line:10%
are a common pattern
of conscious experience

00:06:47.940 --> 00:06:51.600 align:middle line:10%
that occurs to people who
are on the verge of death.

00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:54.630 align:middle line:10%
For example, in a
cardiac arrest from which

00:06:54.630 --> 00:06:57.060 align:middle line:10%
they are resuscitated.

00:06:57.060 --> 00:07:00.480 align:middle line:10%
And basically, they
consist of elements that

00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:02.850 align:middle line:10%
are common all over the world.

00:07:02.850 --> 00:07:06.160 align:middle line:10%
Not every person has
all of the elements.

00:07:06.160 --> 00:07:08.670 align:middle line:10%
But among the things
that people say

00:07:08.670 --> 00:07:12.900 align:middle line:10%
are that they hear the doctors
say something like, oh, my god.

00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:14.010 align:middle line:10%
He's dead.

00:07:14.010 --> 00:07:16.380 align:middle line:10%
Or we've lost her.

00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:19.020 align:middle line:10%
Which is very surprising
to them because they

00:07:19.020 --> 00:07:23.820 align:middle line:10%
say that I have never felt
so alive as when I heard

00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:26.820 align:middle line:10%
that doctor say I was dead.

00:07:26.820 --> 00:07:29.400 align:middle line:10%
Because from their
point of view,

00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:32.370 align:middle line:10%
they feel that they
distance themselves

00:07:32.370 --> 00:07:34.710 align:middle line:10%
from their physical
body and they

00:07:34.710 --> 00:07:37.020 align:middle line:10%
watch the scene of
the resuscitation

00:07:37.020 --> 00:07:40.200 align:middle line:10%
typically from the
point of view above it.

00:07:40.200 --> 00:07:43.590 align:middle line:10%
As this progresses, they
eventually wake up to the fact

00:07:43.590 --> 00:07:47.220 align:middle line:10%
that, oh, this must be
something to do with death.

00:07:47.220 --> 00:07:50.520 align:middle line:10%
And at that point, they enter
into states of consciousness

00:07:50.520 --> 00:07:53.790 align:middle line:10%
that, no matter how
articulate they may be,

00:07:53.790 --> 00:07:55.950 align:middle line:10%
they say there are
no words for it.

00:07:55.950 --> 00:08:00.420 align:middle line:10%
That it's ineffable
or indescribable.

00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:04.650 align:middle line:10%
They go through a passageway
into a beautiful light.

00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:06.810 align:middle line:10%
They feel comfort,
peace, and joy.

00:08:06.810 --> 00:08:10.980 align:middle line:10%
They meet relatives and friends
of theirs who have died.

00:08:10.980 --> 00:08:13.710 align:middle line:10%
And they go through
panoramic memory,

00:08:13.710 --> 00:08:16.110 align:middle line:10%
in which everything
they've ever done

00:08:16.110 --> 00:08:17.850 align:middle line:10%
is displayed around
them in a sort

00:08:17.850 --> 00:08:21.450 align:middle line:10%
of holographic
three-dimensional panorama.

00:08:21.450 --> 00:08:24.510 align:middle line:10%
And they come back
from these experiences

00:08:24.510 --> 00:08:27.360 align:middle line:10%
with a total new take
on life, thinking

00:08:27.360 --> 00:08:30.420 align:middle line:10%
that the most important thing
we can do while we're here

00:08:30.420 --> 00:08:32.580 align:middle line:10%
is to learn how to love.

00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:35.640 align:middle line:10%
And saying that they have
no more fear of death

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:38.490 align:middle line:10%
because they feel that
death is just a transition

00:08:38.490 --> 00:08:41.307 align:middle line:10%
into some other reality.

00:08:41.307 --> 00:08:43.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is that what
happened to you Anita?

00:08:43.140 --> 00:08:43.940 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:45.900 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing when I hear that.

00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:47.040 align:middle line:90%
I think, wow.

00:08:47.040 --> 00:08:48.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You get chills?

00:08:48.150 --> 00:08:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I get chills
because it's like, wow, somebody

00:08:50.610 --> 00:08:51.560 align:middle line:90%
understands me.

00:08:51.560 --> 00:08:53.550 align:middle line:84%
And I've met Raymond
Moody and it was--

00:08:53.550 --> 00:08:54.350 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Great guy.

00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:54.570 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:08:54.570 --> 00:08:56.040 align:middle line:90%
He's such a great guy.

00:08:56.040 --> 00:09:01.740 align:middle line:84%
But when I was out of my body,
I felt so free and light,

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:05.170 align:middle line:84%
and all the pain was gone,
and the fear was gone.

00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:06.960 align:middle line:90%
It just felt amazing.

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:10.410 align:middle line:84%
And I felt powerful
and magnificent.

00:09:10.410 --> 00:09:13.800 align:middle line:84%
And I could see my physical
body lying on the bed,

00:09:13.800 --> 00:09:17.550 align:middle line:84%
and my physical body looked
so small and insignificant

00:09:17.550 --> 00:09:18.900 align:middle line:90%
compared to how I was feeling.

00:09:18.900 --> 00:09:21.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you
were in this state,

00:09:21.090 --> 00:09:23.940 align:middle line:84%
did you notice other
entities around you

00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:24.960 align:middle line:90%
or anything like that?

00:09:24.960 --> 00:09:25.760 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:28.340 align:middle line:84%
I felt I was greeted
by other entities who--

00:09:28.340 --> 00:09:31.140 align:middle line:84%
it felt like they were there
to help me to cross over.

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't recognize all
of them, but one of them

00:09:34.650 --> 00:09:38.670 align:middle line:84%
was my dad who had passed
away 10 years prior to that.

00:09:38.670 --> 00:09:42.810 align:middle line:84%
And it was really amazing
connecting with my dad.

00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:45.360 align:middle line:84%
Because when I was
growing up, I had

00:09:45.360 --> 00:09:48.060 align:middle line:84%
a very turbulent
relationship with my dad.

00:09:48.060 --> 00:09:51.030 align:middle line:84%
But here on the other
side, all I felt from him

00:09:51.030 --> 00:09:53.010 align:middle line:90%
was pure, unconditional love.

00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:54.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's dramatic.

00:09:54.060 --> 00:09:54.860 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:09:54.860 --> 00:09:56.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: In that
state, these 30 hours

00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:59.810 align:middle line:84%
that you were in,
what did you learn

00:09:59.810 --> 00:10:01.160 align:middle line:90%
when you finally came back?

00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:03.980 align:middle line:84%
And tell me about that
experience being rammed back

00:10:03.980 --> 00:10:05.000 align:middle line:90%
into your body.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:06.600 align:middle line:90%
How did that happen?

00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:07.610 align:middle line:90%
Somebody call you?

00:10:07.610 --> 00:10:08.460 align:middle line:90%
Somebody send you?

00:10:08.460 --> 00:10:09.260 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:10:09.260 --> 00:10:11.870 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: My dad sent
me back from that side.

00:10:11.870 --> 00:10:13.550 align:middle line:90%
He told me it wasn't my time.

00:10:13.550 --> 00:10:16.100 align:middle line:90%
He said that I still had gift--

00:10:16.100 --> 00:10:17.570 align:middle line:90%
I had things to do.

00:10:17.570 --> 00:10:20.000 align:middle line:84%
He said I had not
completed my purpose

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:21.148 align:middle line:90%
and I needed to go back.

00:10:21.148 --> 00:10:22.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ah, interesting.

00:10:22.190 --> 00:10:24.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: But I didn't want
to come back because it was so--

00:10:24.740 --> 00:10:26.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's bliss, isn't it?

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.040 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I mean, it
was bliss and my body

00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:30.430 align:middle line:90%
was dying of cancer.

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:32.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Who wants to be
put back into that, right?

00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:34.070 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:36.770 align:middle line:84%
But that's when I started
to learn the lessons.

00:10:36.770 --> 00:10:41.660 align:middle line:84%
I realized that we are
much more powerful than we

00:10:41.660 --> 00:10:43.310 align:middle line:90%
have been led to believe.

00:10:43.310 --> 00:10:46.520 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like it's been
conditioned out of us when

00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:48.080 align:middle line:90%
we're in the physical.

00:10:48.080 --> 00:10:51.380 align:middle line:84%
And I realized my dad--
it was like my dad wanted

00:10:51.380 --> 00:10:54.560 align:middle line:84%
me to know that now that you
know the truth of who you

00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:58.760 align:middle line:84%
really are, you need to go back
and live your life fearlessly

00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:00.950 align:middle line:84%
and your body will
heal dramatically.

00:11:00.950 --> 00:11:03.500 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So when you come
back into this stage four

00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:05.480 align:middle line:90%
cancer-riddened body--

00:11:05.480 --> 00:11:06.590 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:11:06.590 --> 00:11:07.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How did you feel?

00:11:07.720 --> 00:11:09.500 align:middle line:84%
And did you come out
of the coma at all?

00:11:09.500 --> 00:11:11.083 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So I
came out of the coma,

00:11:11.083 --> 00:11:13.010 align:middle line:84%
literally I started
coming out of the coma.

00:11:13.010 --> 00:11:17.670 align:middle line:84%
What it felt like in
linear or human time,

00:11:17.670 --> 00:11:23.930 align:middle line:84%
it felt like that as soon as I
made the decision to come back,

00:11:23.930 --> 00:11:27.680 align:middle line:84%
it felt like I came out of the
coma within minutes after that.

00:11:27.680 --> 00:11:28.890 align:middle line:90%
And as I came out--

00:11:28.890 --> 00:11:29.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But still
with stage four cancer?

00:11:29.950 --> 00:11:31.760 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: Still with
stage four cancer.

00:11:31.760 --> 00:11:33.690 align:middle line:90%
So my body was critical.

00:11:33.690 --> 00:11:36.710 align:middle line:84%
But as I opened my eyes,
and my family was there,

00:11:36.710 --> 00:11:40.130 align:middle line:84%
and my brother had
flown in from India

00:11:40.130 --> 00:11:43.990 align:middle line:84%
because he heard I was
dying, and so he codified.

00:11:43.990 --> 00:11:44.847 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Of course.

00:11:44.847 --> 00:11:45.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:46.610 align:middle line:90%
So he was there.

00:11:46.610 --> 00:11:48.860 align:middle line:84%
And I just started
saying to my family,

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:50.720 align:middle line:90%
I said, I'm not going to die.

00:11:50.720 --> 00:11:51.780 align:middle line:90%
It's not my time.

00:11:51.780 --> 00:11:52.580 align:middle line:90%
Dad is here.

00:11:52.580 --> 00:11:53.780 align:middle line:90%
Dad told me.

00:11:53.780 --> 00:11:56.270 align:middle line:84%
They all thought
I was delirious.

00:11:56.270 --> 00:11:57.800 align:middle line:90%
And so they called the doctor.

00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:01.400 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor said, yes, she's
just-- it's just the drugs.

00:12:01.400 --> 00:12:02.910 align:middle line:90%
It's messing with her mind.

00:12:02.910 --> 00:12:04.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: She's close to going.

00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:05.270 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: She's
close to going.

00:12:05.270 --> 00:12:06.070 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:10.550 align:middle line:84%
So he made sure to not
let my family raise

00:12:10.550 --> 00:12:13.833 align:middle line:84%
their hopes because he was
so sure that I was dying.

00:12:13.833 --> 00:12:16.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you already
proved them wrong on one thing.

00:12:16.250 --> 00:12:18.320 align:middle line:84%
When they said you'd never
come out of the coma.

00:12:18.320 --> 00:12:18.635 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:12:18.635 --> 00:12:19.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And you'd be dead.

00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:22.100 align:middle line:84%
You were still alive and
you came out of the coma.

00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:23.558 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I came
out of the coma,

00:12:23.558 --> 00:12:25.530 align:middle line:84%
but he was still there
saying, she's delirious.

00:12:25.530 --> 00:12:26.330 align:middle line:90%
She's delirious.

00:12:26.330 --> 00:12:28.610 align:middle line:90%
She's still critical.

00:12:28.610 --> 00:12:33.110 align:middle line:84%
But what blew him away, was
then I said to this doctor,

00:12:33.110 --> 00:12:36.080 align:middle line:84%
I said, didn't you take
fluid out of my lungs

00:12:36.080 --> 00:12:37.370 align:middle line:90%
at 5:00 this morning?

00:12:37.370 --> 00:12:38.930 align:middle line:90%
Aren't you the one who did that?

00:12:38.930 --> 00:12:40.430 align:middle line:90%
And he said, how do you know?

00:12:40.430 --> 00:12:41.930 align:middle line:90%
You were in a coma.

00:12:41.930 --> 00:12:44.607 align:middle line:84%
I was able to see and hear
everything that was going--

00:12:44.607 --> 00:12:46.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: As Raymond
Moody pointed out.

00:12:46.190 --> 00:12:46.445 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:12:46.445 --> 00:12:47.737 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You feel those things.

00:12:47.737 --> 00:12:51.410 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And as I started
to like recall, tell them.

00:12:51.410 --> 00:12:53.120 align:middle line:84%
Tell everyone the
conversations that

00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:56.260 align:middle line:84%
were taking place, that's
when they started to realize

00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:58.230 align:middle line:90%
something had happened.

00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:02.930 align:middle line:84%
But what happened is
that after four days,

00:13:02.930 --> 00:13:04.370 align:middle line:90%
I was wanting to sit up.

00:13:04.370 --> 00:13:06.745 align:middle line:84%
I was wanting to take out
the tubes that were in me.

00:13:06.745 --> 00:13:08.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were you
feeling better?

00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:09.495 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I was
feeling better.

00:13:09.495 --> 00:13:10.412 align:middle line:90%
I was still very weak.

00:13:10.412 --> 00:13:11.212 align:middle line:90%
I still--

00:13:11.212 --> 00:13:12.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And still stage four?

00:13:12.620 --> 00:13:15.770 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So in four
days, they took tests.

00:13:15.770 --> 00:13:18.620 align:middle line:84%
Actually, by the fifth
day, they took tests

00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:22.190 align:middle line:84%
and they found that the
tumors had shrunk by 60%.

00:13:22.190 --> 00:13:23.278 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: In four days?

00:13:23.278 --> 00:13:24.320 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: In four days.

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:26.540 align:middle line:90%
And they could not explain it.

00:13:26.540 --> 00:13:30.393 align:middle line:84%
The doctor who was
treating me was blown away.

00:13:30.393 --> 00:13:32.810 align:middle line:84%
He said, I don't even know
what to write in your medical--

00:13:32.810 --> 00:13:34.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They've never
seen anything like this.

00:13:34.070 --> 00:13:34.880 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: They
thought they'd made

00:13:34.880 --> 00:13:36.170 align:middle line:90%
a mistake with the records.

00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:39.440 align:middle line:84%
They thought they had brought
the wrong medical records

00:13:39.440 --> 00:13:41.157 align:middle line:90%
to compare.

00:13:41.157 --> 00:13:42.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they
think the mistake was

00:13:42.740 --> 00:13:45.320 align:middle line:84%
made on the first time when
they called you stage four

00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:47.488 align:middle line:84%
or on the second time when
they said it was gone?

00:13:47.488 --> 00:13:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: Well,
actually, what happened--

00:13:49.280 --> 00:13:49.970 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: In remission.

00:13:49.970 --> 00:13:52.345 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So what happened
was that when-- they send me

00:13:52.345 --> 00:13:54.710 align:middle line:90%
to the lab, to the radiologist.

00:13:54.710 --> 00:13:58.430 align:middle line:84%
And so the radiologist doesn't
have a relationship with me

00:13:58.430 --> 00:14:00.110 align:middle line:90%
and he's just taking the test.

00:14:00.110 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He's just
looking at numbers.

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:02.555 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And he's
just looking at numbers.

00:14:02.555 --> 00:14:06.990 align:middle line:84%
And he's-- and I could hear him
calling my oncologist and said,

00:14:06.990 --> 00:14:08.448 align:middle line:84%
have you sent me
the right records?

00:14:08.448 --> 00:14:09.248 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:14:09.248 --> 00:14:11.450 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: Because when
he made the comparison,

00:14:11.450 --> 00:14:12.480 align:middle line:90%
he said this is not--

00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:15.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: This is not
a stage four person.

00:14:15.080 --> 00:14:15.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:14:15.990 --> 00:14:17.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And were
you alert then?

00:14:17.710 --> 00:14:18.710 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: I was alert.

00:14:18.710 --> 00:14:23.480 align:middle line:84%
I was-- and over the days,
over the next three weeks,

00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:26.610 align:middle line:84%
my work was to build
up my physical stamina.

00:14:26.610 --> 00:14:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Because I now had to build my
strength up and my muscles up

00:14:29.670 --> 00:14:30.470 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:14:30.470 --> 00:14:32.012 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Anita, did
you know what was

00:14:32.012 --> 00:14:33.810 align:middle line:90%
happening to you at this point?

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:37.580 align:middle line:84%
The fact that the cancer was
going away, was in remission.

00:14:37.580 --> 00:14:39.120 align:middle line:90%
You were getting better.

00:14:39.120 --> 00:14:41.880 align:middle line:84%
Were you aware that
you were doing this?

00:14:41.880 --> 00:14:42.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:14:42.680 --> 00:14:44.570 align:middle line:84%
Because what
actually happened is

00:14:44.570 --> 00:14:48.710 align:middle line:84%
that as soon as I came out
of the near-death state,

00:14:48.710 --> 00:14:54.630 align:middle line:84%
I understood that cancer is not
a physical disease of the body.

00:14:54.630 --> 00:15:00.060 align:middle line:84%
It was, for me, it was a
disease from the level of my,

00:15:00.060 --> 00:15:02.400 align:middle line:84%
I guess, from my soul
and my consciousness,

00:15:02.400 --> 00:15:06.930 align:middle line:84%
where I had never allowed
myself to express myself.

00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:10.650 align:middle line:84%
I'd never known how
smart our bodies were.

00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:11.880 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's dramatic.

00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:12.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:15:12.680 --> 00:15:16.440 align:middle line:84%
And so now I knew that
I was already healed,

00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:18.510 align:middle line:84%
but my body just
had to catch up.

00:15:18.510 --> 00:15:21.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Dr. Randy Veitenheimer
was on "The Quantum Effect",

00:15:21.910 --> 00:15:25.110 align:middle line:84%
the Gaia show, talking
about the aspects of death.

00:15:25.110 --> 00:15:26.555 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

