>>RANDY VEITENHEIMER:
Your physical existence

00:15:28.430 --> 00:15:33.530 align:middle line:10%
is a form of the formless in
Chinese philosophy and Taoism.

00:15:33.530 --> 00:15:36.240 align:middle line:10%
Your death is the loss
of the physical form,

00:15:36.240 --> 00:15:40.400 align:middle line:10%
but not the essence of
you, which is life itself,

00:15:40.400 --> 00:15:42.590 align:middle line:10%
our being.

00:15:42.590 --> 00:15:46.760 align:middle line:10%
Life is an expanding
state of awareness.

00:15:46.760 --> 00:15:51.690 align:middle line:10%
Death is an evolving
expression of growth.

00:15:51.690 --> 00:15:56.630 align:middle line:10%
Both are marked by emergence,
life into physical awareness,

00:15:56.630 --> 00:16:01.060 align:middle line:10%
and death into universal
or infinite awareness.

00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:04.720 align:middle line:10%
Life is an imminent
state of being.

00:16:04.720 --> 00:16:07.810 align:middle line:10%
Death is a transcended
state of being.

