and every day he'd walk in with
a black cloud over his head.

00:36:02.450 --> 00:36:05.990 align:middle line:84%
He'd go, this is going to
be a lousy day for me today.

00:36:05.990 --> 00:36:08.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, before the
day even started.

00:36:08.340 --> 00:36:11.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say Howard, what
are you talking about?

00:36:11.070 --> 00:36:12.680 align:middle line:90%
He says, I just can feel it.

00:36:12.680 --> 00:36:13.730 align:middle line:90%
And you know what?

00:36:13.730 --> 00:36:14.810 align:middle line:90%
He had a lousy day.

00:36:14.810 --> 00:36:16.018 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Of course he did.

00:36:16.018 --> 00:36:18.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I think he
brought it onto himself.

00:36:18.290 --> 00:36:22.610 align:middle line:84%
How many people bring these
diseases onto themselves?

00:36:22.610 --> 00:36:24.290 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I think
a lot of people do.

00:36:24.290 --> 00:36:27.740 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, I
don't want them to feel

00:36:27.740 --> 00:36:30.380 align:middle line:84%
it's their fault.
It's not their fault.

00:36:30.380 --> 00:36:32.150 align:middle line:84%
But even though it's
not your fault--

00:36:32.150 --> 00:36:33.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Maybe not directly.

00:36:33.440 --> 00:36:34.482 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Not directly.

00:36:34.482 --> 00:36:37.070 align:middle line:84%
But when you become aware
that you're bringing it

00:36:37.070 --> 00:36:39.820 align:middle line:84%
onto yourself and how you're
bringing it onto yourself,

00:36:39.820 --> 00:36:42.760 align:middle line:84%
that's when you can really
be on the road to healing.

00:36:42.760 --> 00:36:45.790 align:middle line:84%
And so if I had to
explain-- and again,

00:36:45.790 --> 00:36:48.760 align:middle line:84%
words are not enough
to do this justice.

00:36:48.760 --> 00:36:52.550 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to use words that
may sound a little bit woo-woo.

00:36:52.550 --> 00:36:54.490 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, if you
imagine and this

00:36:54.490 --> 00:36:57.830 align:middle line:84%
is how I understood it when
I was on the other side,

00:36:57.830 --> 00:36:59.870 align:middle line:90%
we're not just physical bodies.

00:36:59.870 --> 00:37:03.130 align:middle line:84%
So if you imagine that we
are actually energy bodies

00:37:03.130 --> 00:37:06.880 align:middle line:84%
or energy beings, being
expressed through the physical.

00:37:06.880 --> 00:37:10.660 align:middle line:84%
But what actually matters is
the energy, not the physical.

00:37:10.660 --> 00:37:12.370 align:middle line:90%
That's the more important part.

00:37:12.370 --> 00:37:15.790 align:middle line:84%
If your energy is weak,
your physical body is weak.

00:37:15.790 --> 00:37:19.180 align:middle line:84%
If your energy is strong,
your physical body is strong.

00:37:19.180 --> 00:37:23.650 align:middle line:84%
So the more you do
things that energetically

00:37:23.650 --> 00:37:28.780 align:middle line:84%
make you feel big and powerful,
your body will reflect it.

00:37:28.780 --> 00:37:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And so if you're someone who
is shining bright as an energy,

00:37:33.880 --> 00:37:37.900 align:middle line:84%
if you are someone who knows
I am here as a powerful being,

00:37:37.900 --> 00:37:39.310 align:middle line:90%
good things happen to me.

00:37:39.310 --> 00:37:41.950 align:middle line:84%
And when you feel,
like if you're in love,

00:37:41.950 --> 00:37:43.460 align:middle line:90%
your energy is big.

00:37:43.460 --> 00:37:44.260 align:middle line:90%
When you feel--

00:37:44.260 --> 00:37:46.997 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's like an aura
that just is expanding.

00:37:46.997 --> 00:37:47.830 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:37:47.830 --> 00:37:50.200 align:middle line:90%
It's like an aura expanding.

00:37:50.200 --> 00:37:53.710 align:middle line:84%
And if you feel that you're
destined for good things,

00:37:53.710 --> 00:37:56.090 align:middle line:84%
then your energy
expands accordingly.

00:37:56.090 --> 00:37:58.030 align:middle line:84%
If you know you're
powerful, your energy

00:37:58.030 --> 00:37:59.590 align:middle line:90%
expands accordingly.

00:37:59.590 --> 00:38:02.140 align:middle line:84%
That energy is what
feeds your body.

00:38:02.140 --> 00:38:04.450 align:middle line:84%
That is what fuels
it and gives it

00:38:04.450 --> 00:38:07.750 align:middle line:84%
that health and vibrancy
that actually then does

00:38:07.750 --> 00:38:09.670 align:middle line:90%
bring good things onto you.

00:38:09.670 --> 00:38:12.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you remember the
"Star Trek" television series?

00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:13.080 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:16.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The Doctor Bones
would have this apparatus

00:38:16.480 --> 00:38:20.000 align:middle line:84%
that he'd wave over some sick
person, then they'd be fine.

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:20.800 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:38:20.800 --> 00:38:22.467 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Isn't that
a little bit of what

00:38:22.467 --> 00:38:25.180 align:middle line:84%
you've done by
taking your energy,

00:38:25.180 --> 00:38:28.520 align:middle line:84%
focusing it on certain parts
of your body, and curing it?

00:38:28.520 --> 00:38:29.320 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:38:29.320 --> 00:38:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And although I'll admit,
just like you said,

00:38:31.750 --> 00:38:33.820 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know that's
what I was doing

00:38:33.820 --> 00:38:36.220 align:middle line:84%
and it's more in
hindsight, but yes.

00:38:36.220 --> 00:38:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And to me, I really feel
that medicine of the future

00:38:39.700 --> 00:38:42.880 align:middle line:84%
really needs to go more in
the direction of measuring

00:38:42.880 --> 00:38:46.510 align:middle line:84%
our energy and seeing where
we can expand or increase

00:38:46.510 --> 00:38:50.740 align:middle line:84%
our energy, or helping
us to do things that

00:38:50.740 --> 00:38:54.310 align:middle line:84%
expand our energy because
that is what will actually

00:38:54.310 --> 00:38:55.670 align:middle line:90%
heal our bodies.

00:38:55.670 --> 00:38:57.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I think
the route that you

00:38:57.850 --> 00:39:02.322 align:middle line:84%
took, the chemotherapy,
possibly radiation too as well?

00:39:02.322 --> 00:39:03.530 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: I only had chemo.

00:39:03.530 --> 00:39:05.300 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just the chemo.

00:39:05.300 --> 00:39:07.310 align:middle line:84%
I think that was the
smart thing to do,

00:39:07.310 --> 00:39:10.900 align:middle line:84%
but I would do it in combination
with many of the things we've

00:39:10.900 --> 00:39:12.190 align:middle line:90%
been talking about tonight.

00:39:12.190 --> 00:39:15.580 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Eben Alexander had
a near-death experience

00:39:15.580 --> 00:39:17.058 align:middle line:90%
and came back to talk about it.

00:39:17.058 --> 00:39:19.600 align:middle line:10%
>>EBEN ALEXANDER: I came from
my journey to see the hardships

00:39:19.600 --> 00:39:21.640 align:middle line:10%
and difficulties,
illness and injury,

00:39:21.640 --> 00:39:24.970 align:middle line:10%
are actually the
steppingstones for our growth.

00:39:24.970 --> 00:39:28.540 align:middle line:10%
It's what leads us into
kind of remembering

00:39:28.540 --> 00:39:31.510 align:middle line:10%
the connectedness, the
love of that creative force

00:39:31.510 --> 00:39:33.700 align:middle line:10%
for the creation,
which is basically

00:39:33.700 --> 00:39:36.850 align:middle line:10%
our relationship with our
very conscious awareness

00:39:36.850 --> 00:39:39.760 align:middle line:10%
and with that God force at
the core of the universe

00:39:39.760 --> 00:39:42.935 align:middle line:10%
that so many have
come to realize.

00:39:42.935 --> 00:39:44.560 align:middle line:10%
Not just through
near-death experiences

00:39:44.560 --> 00:39:47.290 align:middle line:10%
and other spiritually
transformative experiences,

00:39:47.290 --> 00:39:51.640 align:middle line:10%
but cultivating that through
a program of meditation

00:39:51.640 --> 00:39:55.640 align:middle line:10%
with a purpose of trying to
learn more about who am I?

00:39:55.640 --> 00:39:56.780 align:middle line:10%
Why am I here?

00:39:56.780 --> 00:39:58.000 align:middle line:10%
Where is this all going?

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:00.250 align:middle line:10%
How can I influence the outcome?

00:40:00.250 --> 00:40:03.550 align:middle line:10%
And each and every one of
us plays a tremendous role.

00:40:03.550 --> 00:40:06.850 align:middle line:10%
In fact, it's one thing that I
try and portray to every soul

00:40:06.850 --> 00:40:11.890 align:middle line:10%
that I encounter, is
everyone is important.

00:40:11.890 --> 00:40:14.350 align:middle line:10%
There is no soul that
is unimportant in this.

00:40:14.350 --> 00:40:17.710 align:middle line:10%
And that includes a lot of the
naysayers and the doubters,

00:40:17.710 --> 00:40:23.200 align:middle line:10%
because they actually present
a very important viewpoint.

00:40:23.200 --> 00:40:27.070 align:middle line:10%
And from my point of view,
as I often say in my talks,

00:40:27.070 --> 00:40:30.520 align:middle line:10%
the best ally in this
journey of deep discovery

00:40:30.520 --> 00:40:32.770 align:middle line:10%
of trying to understand
the nature of consciousness

00:40:32.770 --> 00:40:37.570 align:middle line:10%
and existence, is a true
open-minded skepticism.

00:40:37.570 --> 00:40:40.958 align:middle line:10%
Doubt everything right
down to ground level.

00:40:40.958 --> 00:40:42.250 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: But have an open mind.

00:40:42.250 --> 00:40:44.740 align:middle line:10%
>>ALEXANDER: But have
a very open mind.

00:40:44.740 --> 00:40:47.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Looking at people
like Eben Alexander,

00:40:47.260 --> 00:40:50.560 align:middle line:84%
and you could be up there
on one of our next shows

00:40:50.560 --> 00:40:53.890 align:middle line:84%
as a clip, what do you
do to tell somebody this

00:40:53.890 --> 00:40:56.290 align:middle line:90%
is what I did and I'm here?

00:40:56.290 --> 00:40:57.430 align:middle line:90%
What do you tell them?

00:40:57.430 --> 00:41:00.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I would tell them
that it's really important

00:41:00.580 --> 00:41:03.790 align:middle line:90%
to actually value who you are.

00:41:03.790 --> 00:41:07.600 align:middle line:84%
It's really important to allow
yourself to be who you are,

00:41:07.600 --> 00:41:11.590 align:middle line:84%
be your authentic self,
express yourself fearlessly.

00:41:11.590 --> 00:41:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And it is it's
actually also really

00:41:15.070 --> 00:41:17.530 align:middle line:84%
important to listen
to your intuition

00:41:17.530 --> 00:41:20.530 align:middle line:84%
and to know that you
are much, much more

00:41:20.530 --> 00:41:22.900 align:middle line:90%
than just this physical being.

00:41:22.900 --> 00:41:27.070 align:middle line:84%
And I would also ask people
to work through any fears

00:41:27.070 --> 00:41:28.990 align:middle line:90%
or stresses to heal that.

00:41:28.990 --> 00:41:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Healing the fear of
illness is actually

00:41:31.780 --> 00:41:35.423 align:middle line:84%
more important than
healing the illness itself.

00:41:35.423 --> 00:41:37.840 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I was going say are,
you afraid of dying anymore?

00:41:37.840 --> 00:41:38.500 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: No.

00:41:38.500 --> 00:41:39.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm not afraid of dying.

00:41:39.530 --> 00:41:40.550 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're not in a hurry.

00:41:40.550 --> 00:41:41.450 align:middle line:90%
There's no rush.

00:41:41.450 --> 00:41:42.617 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: There's no rush.

00:41:42.617 --> 00:41:44.770 align:middle line:84%
And I wouldn't encourage
people to go early,

00:41:44.770 --> 00:41:46.060 align:middle line:90%
but I'm not afraid of it.

00:41:46.060 --> 00:41:47.890 align:middle line:84%
They have nothing
to be afraid of.

00:41:47.890 --> 00:41:50.260 align:middle line:84%
And when we heal
our fear of dying,

00:41:50.260 --> 00:41:52.630 align:middle line:84%
we actually heal
our fear of living.

00:41:52.630 --> 00:41:55.565 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you look forward
if that happens again?

00:41:55.565 --> 00:41:56.440 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: To death?

00:41:56.440 --> 00:41:58.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: To the other side?

00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:00.370 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: You know
what's interesting is

00:42:00.370 --> 00:42:04.360 align:middle line:84%
that I love my life now, more
than I did before the NDE.

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:05.650 align:middle line:90%
I love it so much.

00:42:05.650 --> 00:42:06.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You appreciate
it more, don't you?

00:42:06.010 --> 00:42:07.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I
appreciate it more.

00:42:07.910 --> 00:42:10.000 align:middle line:84%
And so on the one
hand, I actually

00:42:10.000 --> 00:42:13.660 align:middle line:84%
look forward to every single
day in my life so much.

00:42:13.660 --> 00:42:17.140 align:middle line:84%
But I don't worry
about death at all.

00:42:17.140 --> 00:42:17.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine.

00:42:17.980 --> 00:42:20.145 align:middle line:84%
When the day comes, I know
I'll go with no regrets.

00:42:20.145 --> 00:42:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think of somebody,

00:42:21.770 --> 00:42:25.000 align:middle line:84%
Anita, who just hates
people, and hates life,

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:26.520 align:middle line:90%
hates their own life?

00:42:26.520 --> 00:42:27.460 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that sad?

00:42:27.460 --> 00:42:28.630 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: That's very sad.

00:42:28.630 --> 00:42:31.300 align:middle line:84%
I feel that they're
missing out on something.

00:42:31.300 --> 00:42:33.850 align:middle line:84%
And I do feel that if
somebody feels that way,

00:42:33.850 --> 00:42:37.810 align:middle line:84%
I feel that it's their
loss, but I would try--

00:42:37.810 --> 00:42:41.920 align:middle line:84%
I would if I was passing them
by, I would give them a hug,

00:42:41.920 --> 00:42:44.770 align:middle line:84%
or say hello, or try
and cheer them up.

00:42:44.770 --> 00:42:48.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And those on the other
side, what do they want for us?

00:42:48.790 --> 00:42:51.940 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: They
actually want us to--

00:42:51.940 --> 00:42:54.970 align:middle line:84%
they want us to love more,
more than anything else.

00:42:54.970 --> 00:42:57.580 align:middle line:84%
There's one thing that's
really lacking in our planet.

00:42:57.580 --> 00:43:00.250 align:middle line:90%
And love, it sounds--

00:43:00.250 --> 00:43:01.720 align:middle line:90%
it's an overused word.

00:43:01.720 --> 00:43:03.100 align:middle line:90%
It's really overused.

00:43:03.100 --> 00:43:07.060 align:middle line:84%
And what Raymond Moody said
about not having the language,

00:43:07.060 --> 00:43:08.740 align:middle line:90%
that is so true.

00:43:08.740 --> 00:43:11.890 align:middle line:84%
Because there is something
that's so ineffable

00:43:11.890 --> 00:43:17.030 align:middle line:84%
that I felt on the other
side and it was so strong,

00:43:17.030 --> 00:43:20.230 align:middle line:84%
and I understood that
we could have it here.

00:43:20.230 --> 00:43:25.510 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that we're
so able to have it,

00:43:25.510 --> 00:43:28.570 align:middle line:84%
but yet there's a
lot of people here

00:43:28.570 --> 00:43:31.690 align:middle line:84%
that are trying to take
it away all the time.

00:43:31.690 --> 00:43:33.920 align:middle line:84%
And it feels like
that all the time.

00:43:33.920 --> 00:43:38.500 align:middle line:84%
And whenever, very often when
we try to share our experience,

00:43:38.500 --> 00:43:41.770 align:middle line:84%
it feels like there's people
who are trying to take it away.

00:43:41.770 --> 00:43:47.080 align:middle line:84%
And like Eben Alexander
said about skeptics,

00:43:47.080 --> 00:43:50.980 align:middle line:84%
skeptics have been great for me,
just like he said, because it's

00:43:50.980 --> 00:43:54.250 align:middle line:90%
made me stronger in my message.

00:43:54.250 --> 00:43:56.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What would
you like viewers

00:43:56.230 --> 00:43:59.900 align:middle line:84%
who are watching this program
right now to take away

00:43:59.900 --> 00:44:01.520 align:middle line:90%
from this show?

00:44:01.520 --> 00:44:04.250 align:middle line:10%
>>MOORJANI: I would like
viewers to know that they

00:44:04.250 --> 00:44:05.960 align:middle line:10%
don't have anything to fear.

00:44:05.960 --> 00:44:08.150 align:middle line:10%
But the main thing
is that I would

00:44:08.150 --> 00:44:12.320 align:middle line:10%
like them to know that they need
to relax, and have more fun,

00:44:12.320 --> 00:44:14.270 align:middle line:10%
and find more joy in life.

00:44:14.270 --> 00:44:15.890 align:middle line:10%
They need to laugh more.

00:44:15.890 --> 00:44:18.300 align:middle line:84%
We've become a culture
or a race of people who

00:44:18.300 --> 00:44:20.540 align:middle line:90%
forgotten how to enjoy life.

00:44:20.540 --> 00:44:22.170 align:middle line:90%
We've forgotten how to have fun.

00:44:22.170 --> 00:44:23.990 align:middle line:90%
We've forgotten how to laugh.

00:44:23.990 --> 00:44:26.430 align:middle line:84%
That's actually more
important than anything.

00:44:26.430 --> 00:44:29.690 align:middle line:84%
And laughing and having
fun and finding your joy

00:44:29.690 --> 00:44:32.510 align:middle line:84%
is actually the best
medicine, even for illness.

00:44:32.510 --> 00:44:35.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's an old saying,
laughter is the best medicine.

00:44:35.110 --> 00:44:35.380 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:44:35.380 --> 00:44:36.260 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that interesting?

00:44:36.260 --> 00:44:36.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it's true.

00:44:36.590 --> 00:44:38.130 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: It is so true.

00:44:38.130 --> 00:44:39.860 align:middle line:90%
It's been overstated.

00:44:39.860 --> 00:44:43.393 align:middle line:84%
It sounds cliche, but it's
actually really, really true.

00:44:43.393 --> 00:44:45.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Anita, thanks for
being on "Beyond Belief."

00:44:45.560 --> 00:44:46.520 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate it.

00:44:46.520 --> 00:44:48.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: Thank you so
much for having me on.

00:44:48.500 --> 00:44:49.417 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: There you go.

00:44:49.417 --> 00:44:55.550 align:middle line:84%
A remarkable subject, a cancer
victim who was in stage four,

00:44:55.550 --> 00:44:57.050 align:middle line:90%
and came to remission.

00:44:57.050 --> 00:44:58.940 align:middle line:90%
And she's here to talk about it.

00:44:58.940 --> 00:45:02.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm George Noory, and thanks
for watching "Beyond Belief."

